<item>
            <title>[WFCORE-365] inconsistent usage of min/max-occurs in model description</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFCORE-365</link>
                <project id="12315422" key="WFCORE">WildFly Core</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The usages of min/max-occurs in the model description are not consistent - e.g. missing in ResourceDescription, mostly wrong when used in the descriptionProvider or outdated examples in the documentation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll attach a simple patch which should actually fix that issue in line with the documentation &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; (incl. recursive usage) and the usage of the CLI (ls -l). However there might be more to it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.jboss.org/author/display/AS71/Description+of+the+Management+Model&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://docs.jboss.org/author/display/AS71/Description+of+the+Management+Model&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
